No

> 
> I would still suggest you do Redfish Validator testing though; the experience will be used in the future

The intent of Redfish service validator is that it runs a large representative number of commands in a short amount of time.  SOME testing is required ("It builds" isn't acceptable) and FWIW, I think that redfish service validator is the easiest, but if there's other stuff that you want to test.
